From c1dafa9994ee5c4ed131b5affbba34d382fa8d7a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Archana Suresh Patil <apatil@sandiego.edu>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 21:23:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] [Model] Add InfLLM-V2 sparse attention backend for
 MiniCPM-SALA

Adds the long-context InfLLM-V2 block-sparse attention path for the
MiniCPM-SALA "minicpm4" layers, used at >= dense_len (8192) context. The
minicpm_sala model transparently uses it when the optional infllm_v2
package is installed and falls back to dense Attention otherwise, so this
is additive on top of the dense model.

Components:
- MiniCPMSALASparseAttentionBackend/Impl/MetadataBuilder: gather full K/V
  from the paged cache, two-tier CompressK scoring, top-k block selection
  (topk + window/block local budget = 96), then infllmv2_attn_varlen_func
  with the selected blocks; dense fallback when no sequence is in the
  sparse regime. Registered under AttentionBackendEnum.CUSTOM.
- HierarchicalCompressedAttentionSpec + manager: KVCacheSpec reporting the
  full-K/V page size (tiers recomputed per step); prefix-cache reuse
  disabled, mirroring MambaManager's rationale.
- Sparse wiring factory that returns the sparse Attention only when
  infllm_v2 is importable.
- Unit tests for config parsing, block-size/page constraints, gather,
  CompressK, metadata builder, mixed-batch dispatch, KV spec/manager,
  and scheduler-spec integration.

page_block_size must be a multiple of 256 (infllm_v2 constraint); sparse
kernels require sm_80+ and the OpenBMB infllmv2_cuda_impl package.

Signed-off-by: Archana Suresh Patil <apatil@sandiego.edu>
